cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a new class of languages based on weak monadic second-order logic.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a likely category as the paper describes the new class of languages in terms of automata.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with infinite words and their properties.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are less likely but still possible as the paper introduces a new class of languages and discusses their properties, which could be relevant to these sub-fields.
